🟡 Simple Factory
One factory → uses if/switch
🟢 Factory Method
Multiple factories → uses polymorphism
🧾 Final Interview Summary (Write This)

Factory Pattern centralizes object creation and returns objects via a common interface, reducing coupling and improving extensibility. It replaces direct object instantiation with a controlled creation mechanism, often supporting the Open/Closed Principle.
